#A Variable is a name given to a memory location in a program
#                 (var=value)

#Rules for Variable Names/Identifiers:
#     Must start with a letter (a-z, A-Z) or an underscore _
#     Can contain letters, digits (0-9), and underscores
#     Cannot be a Python keyword (like if, while, def, etc.)
#     Case-sensitive (Name and name are different)
#     Variable can be of any length


name="hariom"
age=26
height=5.7

#If you want to specify the data type of a variable, this can be done with casting.
a=str(3)     #it will be "3" or '3'
b=int(3)     #it will be 3
c=float(3)   #it will be 3.0

#to print the values
print(name)
print(age)

# to print the type of variable
print(type(name))
print(type(height))

#if we assign any variable to another variable, it will fetch the value of the variable assigned.
age2=age
print(age2)


